          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-X12-002D-line-1" n="1">Lean Tom: when I saw him last week on his horse a-wry</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-X12-002D-line-2" n="2">Threaten'd loudly to turn me to stone w<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.  his sorcery;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-X12-002D-line-3" n="3">But I think little Dan: that in spight of what our Foe says</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-X12-002D-line-4" n="4">He'll find I read Ovid and his Metamorphosis.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-X12-002D-line-5" n="5">For omitting the first (where I make a Comparison</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-X12-002D-line-6" n="6">With a sort of Allusion to Putland and Harrison)</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-X12-002D-line-7" n="7">Yet by my Description You'll find he in short is</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-X12-002D-line-8" n="8">A Pack and a Garran, a Top and a Tortoise</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-X12-002D-line-9" n="9">So I hope for henceforward Y<hi rend="superscript">u</hi> ne'er will ask can I mawl</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-X12-002D-line-10" n="10">This teazing, Conceited, rude, Insolent Animal</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-X12-002D-line-11" n="11">But if this Rebuke might turn to his benefit</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-X12-002D-line-12" n="12">(For I pitty the Man) I should be glad then of it.</l>
          </lg>
        </div>
      </div>
